			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Extension of Taiisien's AE kiting guide (21-27)<a name="27604"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 14 04 1:53 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Hello divas!
<br />
I'm just gonna throw in a few words now after reading the extraordinary guide from Taiisen about AE kite, I tried his advice but since I just started a bard and had only reached 23, I tried to apply his guide to Maru Seru zone and it works! 
<br />

<br />
There are a few kind of mobs to choose there but as long as your outside Netheribian Lair zone or Sanctus Serum zone it is all safe, personally I would choose to be outside Sanctus Serum since the area there is plain and good to run on. 
<br />

<br />
Lots of mobs are roaming outside of the city and since everything is considers indifferently its just to pick which kind of mobs you want and therefor you can be there from 21 to 27 or maybe even longer if you enjoy your stay there. =)
<br />

<br />
When you get there at 21 you can start kite Greyhoppers and when they are turning to light blue just move on to next kind which is the &quot;stonies&quot; and so on. Problem is though, there can be many adds on each kite and if you break circle on a nasty way it can hurt alot but you can feel safe since the zone is near you. Another problem is that you have to watch out so you dont get any other adds that you cant handle, like the hand of seru for an example. But its a big area to run on and you will do great. 
<br />

<br />
The spot is very good to practice on, I sat for 3 hours straight and kept practicing on the &quot;perfect circle&quot;. How? you might wanna ask? Do I suck on twisting so the mobs doesnt get killed? Nope, the thing is that there are always mobs that is roaming around so when you are getting &quot;short&quot; of mobs just get some more, and when you get tired in the fingers just change hand. Piece of cake! 
<br />

<br />
There! Now you got a good practice in bard AE kite and you got yourself to 27 so now got to Taiisien's guide to look for next zone to rule over.
<br />

<br />
Rock on divas!  <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-5.gif" border="0" alt="Wink" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
// Rizie</span></td>
