				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Extension of Taiisien's AE kiting guide (21-27)<a name="33130"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 6 04 9:14 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>thanks for the kind words said here Rizie, i just want to note that the only reason i suggest the cougars in iceclad starting at roughly 25 or so is because this is when you will get resisted far less, also i use iceclad because this allows for the cougar claw  earring  and high quality cougar skins so your bard will not always be poor, lol.  I personally do not suggest ae kiting prior to this level because you want to have some melee skills, or the first time you try and get a group at 35 when you have done so much ae you will die quickly.  However with that being said you can ae kite from level 2 all the way to 65 if you so choose, 2-8 can be done in the shar vahl pit (suggested because all luclin zones have a decient zem) then from level 8 - 25 you can do mobs in Pauladial Caverns (and as a lot of us know this zone has the highest zem in the game).  Anyway i am not critisizing your post i like feedback, just adding some extra info on why i suggest as i did. 
<br />

<br />
Take care and whatever you do in game and life always have fun.</span></td>
